BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:IhaohQ@checkout.tito.io
DTSTAMP:20260506T221915Z
SEQUENCE:1
DTSTART:20260627T090000Z
DTEND:20260627T160000Z
SUMMARY:Supercharged 2026
DESCRIPTION:The 2026 edition of the Tesla Owners UK national member event w
 ill be bigger and better\, with more driving opportunities and a new locat
 ion to enjoy. This new exciting location will host our Supercharged Centra
 l in the Millbrook Concept 1 building\, with a great space for talks and p
 anel debates\, a big hard surface for our Concours d'Elegance\, children's
  activities and display cars\, and a range of or partners and suppliers at
 tending too. And for the first time\, we have a range of fantastic driving
  experiences to access. Your ticket will include a chance to drive the ico
 nic Alpine Course and the High Speed Bowl\, and if you want to try out the
  acceleration and speed of your Tesla\, you can buy the optional One-Mile 
 Straight add-on. Entry to Supercharged is free for our paid supporters\, a
 nd payable for free and non-members. This will be a family friendly event.
  One ticket is required per car irrespective of passenger numbers\, though
  track access is for the TOUK member only. Please add the additional One M
 ile Straight ticket if you wish to access that optional experience. SUPERC
 HARGED 2026 HIGHLIGHTS • Technical talks and panel discussions • New owner
  sessions • Mini Tesla track for children • Accessories and merchandise • 
 Great food and drink • Demonstrations • Concours d’elegance • Modified Tes
 la display • Special parking for Model X and Roadster • Driving experience
 s with your own car Please note all ticket sales are final and refunds wil
 l only be given if the event is cancelled by TOUK. Important Notes if you 
 wish to take part in the driving experience elements: Access to the drivin
 g experiences will be subject to a number of rules as you might image to e
 nsure your safety\, and to make sure all attendees have their opportunity 
 to enjoy the day! By completing your ticket purchase\, you acknowledge you
  have red and understood the following: You must have a valid UK licence. 
 (we are checking if EU licenses are acceptable). You must not have anyone 
 under 16 in the car (children are very welcome at the rest of the event bu
 t you must have an adult with them at all times). No alcohol is permitted 
 at Millbrook. In all cases it is the responsibility of the car owner/polic
 y holder to contact their insurer to ensure that the policy they hold does
  indeed cover the Millbrook driving day. Additionally\, even if a policy h
 as Track day cover do not assume it covers you automatically it is usually
  a requirement of the policy that you notify the insurer in advance. Any d
 amage caused to UTAC property will be invoiced to the Member. There will b
 e compulsory attendance at a safety briefing and you will be required to s
 ign an indemnity waiver before receiving your wristband that will gain you
  access to the tracks. If you wish to access the One Mile Straight\, you m
 ust already have your driver briefing wrist band\, and then validate your 
 optional ticket with TOUK event control to gain your special second wrist 
 band. We recommend that you buy this optional ticket with your main entry 
 ticket as we can’t guarantee space on the day. The event is not a track da
 y or MSA approved\, and no helmets required. There is no timing and speed 
 limits are applied\, it is a driving experience on private roads. Speed li
 mits applied are 100mph on the High Speed Bowl and 55mph on the Alpine Cou
 rse\, that may sound low but it's very steep and twisty in places. Once yo
 u leave the Supercharged Central area\, you must not deviate from the appr
 oved routes as described in the driver briefing\, and you must not stop or
  exit your car unless instructed to do so by a marshal. All track experien
 ces are managed by UTAC. Their decision is final on all aspects of track a
 nd driver safety. If there is any dangerous driving observed\, not only wi
 ll you be ejected from the tracks (and no refunds given)\, you put the who
 le club at risk of using the site in future. You will have a ½ hour slot t
 o enjoy the Alpine Circuit and the high speed bowl. If we become oversubsc
 ribed this may be reduced to ensure all members get a chance. If spaces ar
 e free towards the end of the day\, you may get a second opportunity so do
  listen out for announcements\, but we expect the experiences to be popula
 r and we want to ensure all members get a fair chance to enjoy the tracks.
  Any cars not observing the recommended experience time will be red flagge
 d by the marshals and will lose their opportunity to take part in future d
 riving events. If you are taking part in the Concours d’Elegance\, we will
  be keeping a slot free late afternoon so that you can take part in the dr
 iving experiences once the show cars are released from the static part of 
 Supercharged Central at about 3pm. While we endeavour to enable all member
 s with valid tickets who meet the driving requirements to experience the c
 ourses\, this will be subject to availability on the day and priority will
  be for Supporter Members\, and those who have purchased a one mile straig
 ht ticket. We do not want any re-enactments of the James Bond Casino Royal
  crash (which was filmed in the Alpine Course).\n\nListing: June 27th\, 20
 26\n\nWall clock / source TZ: Europe/London\n\nEvent & tickets (Ti.to): ht
 tps://ti.to/teslaownersuk/supercharged-2026\n\nSource list: upcoming\n\nTi
 .to DTSTAMP: 2026-05-06T22:19:13+00:00\n\nTesla Owners UK: https://ti.to/t
 eslaownersuk\n\nClub site: https://teslaowners.uk/
CREATED:20251216T171953Z
LAST-MODIFIED:20260409T161806Z
